👉 We had an amazing conversation featuring an industry expert in aesthetics, Jonathan McLean, MHR - Aesthetic Healthcare Consultant, the CEO of Mclean Aesthetics . Take a moment to enjoy the episode and Let’s Cover That!

Full episode links in the comments!

In this episode, we discuss:

⭐Jonathan’s background in staffing and recruiting led him to discover a demand for talented professionals in the med spa and aesthetic industry, inspiring him to establish McLean Aesthetics.

🏆 When selecting candidates, Jonathan seeks individuals who are passionate about building a brand and delivering exceptional results. Continuous training and skill development are vital in this field.

👥 Jonathan shared strategies for building a high-performing team, including defining goals, offering competitive compensation, and fostering a positive work environment aligned with the promises made during the hiring process.

🏉 We discussed the challenges faced by entrepreneurs entering the med spa industry and emphasized the importance of understanding the business side of aesthetics. Community-building, diverse marketing efforts, and prioritizing staff well-being were highlighted as key factors for success. 

This episode is sponsored by: CM&F Group

This week we interview physician assistant Dani Sher, PA-C. Dani is an aesthetic injector, ultrasound instructor, ER physician associate, and improv comedian in Illinois. She transitioned from the ER / Trauma in hospitals to aesthetics. She is the founder and CEO of Sparkle Aesthetics. Sparkle Aesthetics is a ‘Jetsons’ themed aesthetic practice. Being born in the 70s and watching various shows that showed classy and elegant beauty from that period inspired her to design her medspa as such. She talks about the Zoom Boom, Face-Mapping and her trademark, her credited in-training courses, her getting into comedy, 

Dani is the Found/CEO and aesthetic injector at Sparkle Aesthetics, located in Oak Park, IL. She notes that they frequent procedures like botox, filler, kybella, PRP, morpheus, radio frequency techniques, micro-needling, sculptra, and more in the Oak Park area. 

Personal Instagram: @dani_sparkle_pa

Business Instagram: @sparkleaestheticsoakpark

Business Website: sparkleaesthetics.com

If you’re looking to build your brand and make a name for yourself in the aesthetic industry, it’s time to level up your networking game.
Attending conferences, workshops, and educational events is crucial for staying up-to-date with the latest techniques and advancements in aesthetic injections.
Not only will you gain valuable knowledge, but you’ll also have the opportunity to connect with fellow professionals and industry leaders.
Remember, building your brand goes beyond just providing exceptional services. It’s about establishing yourself as an expert and trusted authority in the field.
So, mark those conference dates on your calendar, pack your business cards, and get ready to take your aesthetic injecting career to new heights!

This week we interview nurse practitioner and business owner Shy Smith FNP-C. 

Shy got started on her aesthetic-injecting journey between 2017-2018. The practice she was working at in Las Vegas invited Allergan representatives to train the employees, which helped expose her to a lot of knowledge in injecting. 

Shortly after training, she studied for her Nurse Practitioner license to begin injectables. Around 2020 she decided to open her own medical spa, Nurse Cosmetics. 

Shy wanted to educate people around her that getting injectables can look very natural and has anti-aging benefits. 

Shy advises what injectable procedures people should look into when first getting work done. Shy learned very quickly that managing an aesthetic Medspa  is challenging, and it’s essential to have a solid team behind you, help them excel, and for them to see your vision. 

Instagram: @nursiecosmeticsco
Website: https://www.nursiecosmeticsbeauty-spa.com/

Question: How Important is training and continuous  education ? 

I loved this answer so much, because @thewhitecoatbeauty  describes the hustle that it takes to be a great injector, even when you are working in the field. 

Once you are able to establish an injector opportunity, I believe that is essential to make yourself uncomfortable by putting yourself out into the industry. 

If you want to excel in your career, you have to 

1. Invest in yourself, like @thewhitecoatbeauty mentioned, after hours or weekend courses may be necessary to get the education that is needed.

2. Never stop trainning and going to conferences, you do not know the information, that you don’t know and you are not going to figure it out in your office. TAKE THE RISK ! 

Check out some great resources, I would recommend below for trainning ;

💉 @theclinicusa

Question: How Important is the trust between the patient and  the Injector ? 

I loved this answer so much, because @needle_daddy speaks about the trust you must have with your patients to keep them coming back. Building a clientele starts with transparency. 

This interview is filled with many gems, however I wanted to highlight this point, because it is so crucial. 

If you do not have patients coming in to sit in your chair, it is just an expensive hobby. 

The art of not just advertising to get patients through the door, but giving them an experience that they will never forget, is a skillset. 

Remember guys, this is a private pay business, so clients notice everything, if they are spending to come see you. 

If you are struggling to define your brand, this could potentially be the problem. 

#aesthetics #botox #dermalfiller #la #mcleanaeathetics #picsoftheday #photooftheday #aesthetics #botox #mcleanaesthetics #theaesthetictalk #podcast #rewind

If you want to grow in your professional career, find a great mentor. 

I have been lucky enough to have some great mentors in my career, that have helped me to establish my business and my influence in the industry. 

The key to finding a great mentor is simple, find someone that is like minded and has more experienced than you. Someone that has already went through the hurdles and wants to genuinely help you. 

Shoutout to every single person that has guided me, took the time out to have lunch with me, shared business tips or just simply picked up the phone to give me advice on how they would handle certain situations. 

As professionals, we are always going to have adversity, however it is truly your community around you that helps you to fight and overcome the challenges that may arise. 

#aesthetics #botox #dermalfiller #mcleanaesthetics #viral #photofotheday #picsoftheday #dermatology #hiring

⏪ Eposide Rewind ⏪

Question: What advice would you give to new injectors entering the industry ? 

I loved the answer that @baileysbotox gave, because it is true! Community is your strength in this industry. 

It can be hard in the beginning to find your tribe within the industry, but keep going ! Reach out to providers on Instagram, go to conferences and connect with others at trainings. 

Every Injector that you see at the top of there game, has built a strong community around them. No one can achieve a great amount of success without the help of others, we are all learning each day. 

Don’t give up hope, keep going. I promise you, if you put the work in, it will happen.

It doesn’t matter, apply for the position anyways. 

When a company puts out an ad for a new employee, it is a wishlist of what they are looking for in a future candidate. 

However many factors play a role in a company hiring a candidate, so no exact resume or experience grantee’s you the position. 

Take the risk, the worst the company can say is no. You will also be one step closer to achieving your goal.

Nurse Christy & Nurse Emma 
This week we interview the mother/daughter duo “Nurse Christy” and “Nurse Emma” based out of the NY/ NJ area. 

Christine Adams, MBA, MSN, NP-BC, CANS aka “Nurse Christy” founded SkinSplendid to create a place where patients could come for concierge aesthetic treatments and not feel rushed or pushed into procedures that were not right for them. Christy wanted to create services that were result oriented and left patients feeling good. 
Instagram: @nursechristynyc

Emma Adams, BSN, RN aka “Nurse Emma” took after her mother and joined SkinSplendid shortly after. Nurse Emma invests in her patients’ overall happiness and well-being through skincare and injectables. She continues to develop her skills under the mentorship of Nurse Christy. 
Instagram : @nurseemmanyc

Both guest gives tips on offering five-star service and how to find the right clientele for your spa. Jonathan also tested both guests on his newest segment, “Red Flag or Green Flag,” “The Hot Seat,” and “Ask the Expert”.
